race.comment: BOHEMIAN DIAMOND (7) looks on song following a recent trial win at Belmont and she boasts a very strong fresh record. She was a winner first-up last campaign as an odds-on favourite and this looks to shape similarly. Can lob just off the speed and return with a bang once again. RIPPER FAROOQ (9) has been superb since joining the new stable, missing out by 0.6L at this track and trip just 10 days ago. Harder here, but maps ideally from the inside draw and he should be hitting his peak third-up. Can go one better now. RETURN OF THE MACH (11) drops back to 1200m now following a disappointing run last time out. She's likely to get back in the run, but she's a progressive type and she'll be flying home late in the race. SUNBRONZED (4) can be in the finish once again as this shapes similarly to his latest effort. MANHATTAN STRIP (3) gets CJP in the irons now and can make his presence felt.
